## Critical — Filename Standards

Format: `[service/subject]-[location]-[context].webp`

- Lowercase only — no capitals ever
- Hyphens only — no spaces, underscores, special characters
- No generic names — no `image1.webp`, `hero.webp`, `photo.webp`
- No typos — spell-check every filename
- Format: `.webp` — never `.png` or `.jpg` as primary source
- Length: 3–8 words maximum

See `references/image-naming.md` for naming patterns by page type.

## Critical — Alt Text Standards

Formula: `[What is happening] + [who/what involved] + [location where natural]`

- Maximum 125 characters
- No duplicated words in the string
- No keyword stuffing — write for visually impaired users first
- Include city/area name where it fits naturally
- Never start with "Image of" or "Photo of"
- Never leave alt empty on meaningful images — only decorative get `alt=""`
- Never truncate — must be a complete sentence

**Examples:**
- ✅ `"Gas Safe engineer checking boiler pressure during annual service in Peterborough"`
- ✅ `"Plumber fixing a burst pipe under a kitchen sink in a Peterborough home"`
- ❌ `"boiler service"` (too generic)
- ❌ `"professional boiler service service in Peterborough"` (duplicate word)

## Critical — Next.js Image Props

Every `<Image>` MUST have:

```tsx
<Image
  src="/images/[filename].webp"
  alt="[descriptive alt text]"
  width={[px]}
  height={[px]}
  sizes="[responsive sizes string]"
  priority={true | omit}    // true ONLY on first hero per page
  quality={85}               // 75–85 for photos
/>
```

### priority rules
- First hero image on page: `priority={true}`
- ALL other images: omit priority entirely (defaults to lazy)
- NEVER set `priority={true}` on cards, below-fold, or secondary images
- NEVER manually set `loading="eager"`

### sizes by layout
- Full-width hero: `sizes="100vw"`
- Two-column: `sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 50vw"`
- Three-column cards: `sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, (max-width: 1024px) 50vw, 33vw"`

### width × height by type
- Hero: `width={1200} height={675}` (16:9)
- Service card: `width={400} height={300}` (4:3)
- Blog hero: `width={1200} height={630}` (OG ratio)
- Team photo: `width={600} height={600}` (1:1)

## Important — Hero Blur Placeholder

Add `placeholder="blur"` + `blurDataURL` to hero images:

```tsx
import { getPlaiceholder } from 'plaiceholder'
const { base64 } = await getPlaiceholder('/images/services/boiler-service-peterborough.webp')

<Image
  src="/images/services/boiler-service-peterborough.webp"
  alt="Gas Safe engineer carrying out annual boiler service in Peterborough"
  width={1200} height={675} sizes="100vw"
  priority={true} quality={85}
  placeholder="blur" blurDataURL={base64}
/>
```

## Important — OG / Social Share Images

- Format: JPG (not WebP — some platforms reject it)
- Dimensions: 1200 × 630px exactly
- Location: `/public/images/og/[page-slug].jpg`
- Every page needs a unique OG image
- Keep important content centred — edges get cropped on mobile

## Important — Image Schema

Add `image` property to Service and Article JSON-LD schemas:

```json
"image": {
  "@type": "ImageObject",
  "url": "https://[domain]/images/services/[filename].webp",
  "width": 1200, "height": 675,
  "caption": "[Descriptive caption]"
}
```

